Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: The Girl Who Lived in the Tree (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Alexander McQueen created a fairy tale about a feral girl who becomes a princess for his autumn/winter 2008 collection The Girl Who Lived in the Tree (look pictured)?

entry.title: an Iowa TV station (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that an Iowa TV station paid Tom Brokaw, a future anchor of NBC Nightly News, $75 a week to work as a staff announcer and part-time newscaster?

entry.title: Jenna Winebrenner (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a men's soccer team hired Jenna Winebrenner to analyze game film and practice with the squad?

entry.title: UDC Homes (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that shareholders of UDC Homes received two settlements over claims that executives sought to inflate its stock price and conceal financial information?

entry.title: imamate (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that in Zaydi Shi'ism, the imamate was not inherited or appointed but had to be claimed by public summons for allegiance or even leadership of an armed revolt?

entry.title: Been Like This (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Meghan Trainor had been a fan of T-Pain for a long time before they finally collaborated on the song "Been Like This" from her upcoming sixth major-label studio album, Timeless?

entry.title: Crossing a Line (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Crossing a Line compares Palestinian political expression on either side of the Green Line between Israel and the occupied Palestinian territories?

entry.title: Longlac (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the town of Longlac was originally founded as a North West Company trading post circa 1800?

entry.title: Syncletica of Alexandria (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Syncletica of Alexandria, a 4th-century saint and Desert Mother, was called "an upper-class girl who does not care about her body"?
